  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0da2\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0d86\u0dba\u0dad\u0db1 \u0dc0\u0dbd \u0db8\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd4\u0da7\u0dd4 \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dad\u0dda \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dc3\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0db1\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Stops arbitrary change of heads of government institutions",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "President Ranil Wickramasinghe has appointed a committee to obtain prior approval for new appointments or changes to the positions of chairman and director of state corporations, statutory boards and state-owned enterprises.",
        "Chief Secretary Anura Dissanayake, Cabinet Secretary W.M.D.J. Messrs. Fernando and Mr.",
        "Mr. Chaminda Kularatne, Additional Secretary to the President, has been appointed as the secretary of the committee.",
        "If it is necessary to change the positions of chairman and board of directors of state corporations, statutory boards and state-owned enterprises, it is mandatory to submit nominations to the above committee with justifiable reasons and obtain prior approval.",
        "This committee has been appointed by focusing on the written requests made to the President from time to time and some informal appointments to change the positions of chairman and board of directors of state corporations, statutory boards and state-owned enterprises without prior agreement.",
        "In this regard, a letter has been sent directly to all the secretaries of the ministries with the signature of the President's Secretary, and copies have been sent to the Prime Minister's Secretary and the Ministry of Finance, Economic Stabilization and National Policy for making the necessary arrangements."
      ],
